{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Place butter and flour in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add water then pulse <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/2-4 times<b> until just clinging together. Tip out, form into a ball then wrap in cling film and chill for 30 minutes.","Roll out pastry on a lightly floured surface and use to line 6 tartlet tins (Ø 8-9 cm). Prick bases with a fork, then return to fridge for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C. Line pastry shells with baking paper and fill with baking beans then blind bake for 10-15 minutes (180°C) until baking paper can be removed easily. Remove beans and paper then bake for a further 10 minutes (180°C) until golden."]},{"title":"Mushroom Duxelle","content":["Place shallot and butter in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add mushrooms then sauté <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add parsley, thyme, salt and pepper then blend <b>5 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then blend again <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and drizzle with truffle oil. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Stilton Rarebit","content":["Place beer, Stilton and Cheddar in mixing bowl then heat <b>3 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>.","Add breadcrumbs, flour, egg, egg yolk, mustard and Worcestershire sauce then cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl to cool. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Celeriac Purée","content":["Place celeriac, cream, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then cook <b>20 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>. Meanwhile, divide reserved mushroom duxelle between pastry cases then spread a heaped tablespoon of reserved rarebit on top of each. Keep purée warm after cooking.","Bake tartlets for 10-15 minutes (180°C) until golden brown. Meanwhile, place steaks on a baking tray. Brush all over with a little olive oil then season with 1 pinch salt and 1 pinch black pepper per side. Roast (see tip) for 4-6 minutes (220°C), turning once, until cooked to taste, then cover with foil and rest for a minimum of 5 minutes. To serve, carve each fillet and serve on a plate with a tartlet and some celeriac purée scattered with chopped parsley."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["70 g salted butter, cold, diced","140 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","40 g water, chilled"]},{"title":"Mushroom Duxelle","content":["1 shallot, halved","10 g butter","200 g chestnut mushrooms, halved","3 - 5 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","1 sprig fresh thyme, leaves only","¼ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","5 g truffle oil"]},{"title":"Stilton Rarebit","content":["40 g beer","75 g Stilton, cut in pieces","100 g Cheddar cheese, extra mature, cut in pieces","30 g breadcrumbs","10 g plain flour","1 medium egg","1 egg yolk, from medium egg","2 tsp English mustard","1 dash Worcestershire sauce"]},{"title":"Celeriac Purée","content":["600 - 700 g celeriac (1 whole celeriac), peeled , cut in pieces (2-3 cm)","380 g whipping cream","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper"]},{"title":"","content":["6 pieces beef fillet (175-200 g each)","olive oil, for brushing","fine sea salt, for seasoning steak","ground black pepper, for seasoning steak","2 Tbsp fresh parsley, leaves only, chopped, for garnish"]}],"id":"r130143","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-MeIMsE0y2Ig\/XZQu3xlilSI\/AAAAAAAAcYA\/FzTrt5XJOSoxOOUoBVmn9IgwMWerCIuwQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8-CiMGii2kwcwBTU.png","title":"Fillet of Beef, Mushroom and Stilton Rarebit Tarts with Celeriac Purée","publishedAt":"2016-12-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"51.3 g","fat":"56.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.3 g","calories":"3473 kJ \/ 830 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, small tartlet tins (Ø 9 cm), baking beans, baking paper, rolling pin, aluminium foil, baking tray, pastry brush, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["If you have a double oven, preheat one to 180°C and one to 220°C, otherwise you can cook the s